    "A widely accepted 104,271, alternative design to minimize this problem consists in dividing the large crossbars into smaller ones (Supplementary Fig. 9b), whose reduced size improves their read margin (that is the portion of the applied voltage in the inputs that is actually delivered to the memristors).",
